('31762622', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Good but could be better', 'I find this app very hard to use when I am driving, particularly if I wish to input a hazard. I think it should operate more by voice recognition to be truly useful. \n\nI also find that Waze is sufficiently popular to cause a lemming-like traffic jam. I recently drove to Florida from Pennsylvania via Nashville and found that if I ignored Waze alternate route I was better off. \n\nAlso, although this problem may be due to my age, I found it quite difficult to set so that IPhone\'s power saver mode wouldn\'t constantly lock down and shut off the screen. It was not an intuitive resolution for ME. \n\nRegardless of the aforementioned I like the app but IMHO, it could be better.', '169444437', 'applestore', 'France', 'Worse and worse', 'This app was the best GPS app until it was bought by Google, I advertised it to all my loved ones. The problem is that now we are trying to get through the main roads instead of taking the shortest route. Why do you think ? Because Google places advertising on the app and they have more to gain from getting past the signs of their customers. It is a shame: to redeem what is made better to make it a machine with money to the detriment of the user. Again this morning, on the journey I take every day to get to the Waze station wanted to get me through a road that made me lose 7 minutes on a 25 minute ride. If I had listened to him I missed my train. The most serious is that the fastest way I take it every day, Waze is supposed to learn from our habits. Well, that was what it was before. I really regret the Waze of the time and I wanted to point out here that by continuing thus this indispensable application will become useless when the users will have understood that your goal is no longer to help us to avoid the traffic jams and to find the fastest way . Please change this as soon as possible and give us our Waze!', 'Waze', 0.24497, 1, 1, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'all', 133, 0, 1, 0.875, 'ot', 'ot'),
