('108055571', 'applestore', 'United States', 'No way', 'Waze has been a good app until the recent update but in the past few months it become more intrusive and a road safety hazard. The app is nosy as it now wants to access the contact list, pops up more in your face ads, and wants to run in the background to track your movement. Compromising the driving experience with intrusive ads is a total no. Tracking me after I arrived at the destination is also not this app business. This is a GPS app and not a social network gateway app. For this reason I regret upgrading this app. Nothing good lasts forever.', '100734254', 'applestore', 'France', 'Signals when there is no network', 'Pb when there is no network: Would it be possible to signal a radar, object, danger even when off-grid? For example, I am off the network so I am pointing out an obstacle, the app keeps in memory the location and the report then sends it as soon as I have network again.  The radars: Yes, yes, as we know, the law prohibits the location of radars, just as rolling without a belt is forbidden but anyone who wants to take the risk can ride without anyway. Now, free to each to activate or not this function that allows the application via its programming code. This app was the best thanks to this function, now it\'s a gps like any other ...', 'Waze', 0.229286, 1, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 360, 0, 0, 1, 'ot', 'ot'),
('108626751', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Looking for a new app', 'I\'ve been a wazer for years. Now I am looking for another option to do what it did so well. Sure it still works but now there are only 2 settings in terms of access to my location- always or never. I do not want it operating in the background paying attention to my location when I am not even driving. Turning it to \"never\" when I leave the car, turning it to \"always\" when I return is a temporary fix. Not acceptable.', '100734254', 'applestore', 'France', 'Signals when there is no network', 'Pb when there is no network: Would it be possible to signal a radar, object, danger even when off-grid? For example, I am off the network so I am pointing out an obstacle, the app keeps in memory the location and the report then sends it as soon as I have network again.  The radars: Yes, yes, as we know, the law prohibits the location of radars, just as rolling without a belt is forbidden but anyone who wants to take the risk can ride without anyway. Now, free to each to activate or not this function that allows the application via its programming code. This app was the best thanks to this function, now it\'s a gps like any other ...', 'Waze', 0.201669, 0, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 361, 0, 0, 1, 'ot', 'ot'),
