('117866791', 'applestore', 'United States', 'It won\'t let me review cause of my one star', 'Wow Spotify. Screw YOU for you completely taking all freedom from people who AREN\'T premium listeners. I used to try to find new music and new artists on here. I would search an artist, listen to a few of their top songs, then either add them to my own playlist, or keep searching.\n\nNOW, I can\'t even decide which songs I want to listen to from ANY artist. I can\'t listen to the top songs of my choice, I can\'t even search one song and just listen to that!!!!!!!\n\nWhat assholes!!! \nI suggest everyone go to SoundCloud, where you can listen to any music you choose, and skip as much as you like!!!!', '487593250', 'applestore', 'France', 'Good', 'Good but when you can not pay to have spotify premium and bah you can not listen to the music out wifi and the titles pass randomly obligatory ... One can only pass a certain number of music before to no longer be able to pass.', 'Spotify', 0.222788, 2, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 372, -1, 1, 0.75, 'br', 'ot'),
('11880257', 'applestore', 'United States', 'It\'s free', 'Great when it alerts you to traffic, which is the main reason I use it on my commute.  But when used for directions to a new place, it could be improved.  A bit more warning for the upcoming turns and to include street names in the audio.', '148608914', 'applestore', 'France', 'Indispensable', 'I use it practically every time I leave the car. The arrival time is much closer to reality than to the integrated GPS of my car and this from the validated destination. The traffic information is interesting although it is obviously impossible to verify if the diversion of the route has been beneficial.  On the other hand, the report of danger is still laborious and dangerous enough for my taste. It is not known what heading to choose and therefore either one leaves the road of the eyes easily or one abandons the report.  Finally the programming of a course to stage is galley and the map of choice of the courses does not take into account the steps. Well, it\'s just about anything.', 'Waze', 0.168241, 2, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 373, 1, 0, 0.875, 'ot', 'ot'),
