('138697472', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Crazy data usage', 'I have Spotify premium. I\'ve had it for years. For the first time ever I\'ve run into this problem: my cellular data usage went off the charts this week. Nearly used up my whole quota of 20 GB within 6 days. So to determine what was going on, I restarted my phone and reset my data statistics in the morning and went about my day like normal which includes some travel time and listening to music on and off wifi. Needless to say, I have my playlists saved offline which is the one reason I\'ve paid for Spotify premium for years. Today alone, I used nearly 1 GB of data alone; for listening to one playlist stored offline. I don\'t know what gives but I know for a fact Spotify has been killing my data usage and the rest of my apps and even system usage has been rather low or as expected. Nearly 1GB in a day for listening to nothing but the same offline playlist while also being on wifi atleast 30% of the time? Yea. This needs to be fixed ASAP.', '133315165', 'applestore', 'France', 'Super but takes up space', 'Spotify has become my only source of music. I use it in premium mode (included in my phone subscription). Most of the time, I listen to it in 4g / wifi, but the offline mode is very convenient on the move. Playlists are varied and good. The radio mode, which allows to listen to songs &quot;similar&quot; to a given piece, is very good because it follows my desires of the moment. Only problem (which costs a star), the space occupied by the app increases very quickly, even without downloading many songs, without my understanding why. Unable to &quot;clean&quot; the app data. Only solution I found, remove regularly and reinstall the app.', 'Spotify', 0.223494, 1, 1, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 383, 0, 1, 0.875, 'br', 'ot'),
