('15097847', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Great App, Poor Execution', 'Waze is a fantastic app with some very powerful things going on in the background to route you away from known traffic jams and accidents.  It\'s full of great and entertaining features that make commuting easier, whether it a long trip or your daily commute to work.  \n\nHowever, it seems there is too much going on for some phones and tablets to handle. This is especially true if you intend to stream other media while doing so.  I travel in rental cars from time to time and have had the chance to try the app in conjunction with different auto manufacturers bluetooth services, and there are some things left to be desired regardless of what I\'m driving. most notably is how the driving instructions interrupt what you are listening to, the lack of volume control over those instructions, and how sometimes the app crashes and you don\'t realize you\'ve missed directions. \n\nFurther frustrations come from the amount of power clearly used by this app for location services. I notice a stark difference when I allow location services to Waze and when I do not allow them.\n\nI hope to raise my rating in the future, but at this point I cannot discount the frustrations I\'ve experienced in a variety of situations involving Waze.', '341013077', 'applestore', 'France', 'Very convenient.', 'Easy-to-use app Very reliable GPS', 'Waze', 0.0690125, 1, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 387, 0, 0, 1, 'ot', 'fr');
