('21548267', 'applestore', 'United States', 'What happened? Routing is messed up.', 'Something happened recently with the quality of this app. It used to always take me on the fastest route, but now I have to ignore Waze every time and do what I think is best. It will try to turn me around multiple times, until it finally realizes what I\'m trying to do. Then it will finally switch to my route and shave off a few minutes. What happened that it\'s not selecting the best route anymore? I\'ve been using Waze for 7 years, and have had royalty status for a long time. Now I\'m considering not using it. Please fix this routing issue ASAP!', '105747713', 'applestore', 'France', 'Very good', 'I find Waze very well done. I only put 3 stars because months ago a red dot appears showing me 8 messages that I could never read. It is not because I have an iPhone 4 that I should no longer have access to this function. Otherwise super', 'Waze', 0.0887479, 0, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 439, 2, 2, 1, 'br', 'ot'),
('221208813', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Location service Always On?? Really?', 'Every other App has an option only to use location services WHILE THE APP IS OPEN. Waze has two options, enable location services manually in settings every time you want to use it, or most of the users who don\'t know are using up their battery by keeping it on all of the time (yes, even after you close out of the app in multitasking).  Google who bought Waze uses this data for better location accuracy for Google Maps but leaves it in the fine print. If you have Waze on your phone you are using up your battery all day long to help Google Maps users get better locational information. Boo! Two thumbs down', '78034301', 'applestore', 'France', 'Permanent Location &amp; Big Battery Console', 'Even when the application is turned off Waze uses your location data. No possibility to activate the location in mode &quot;when the app is active&quot;. So locating and exchanging permanent data: it eats the battery and I do not want to be tracked down.', 'Waze', 0.236141, 3, 1, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 440, 2, 0, 0.75, 'ot', 'ot'),
