('86792951', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Pretty good, but...', 'Not a hard core user but find it pretty good. I generally use it concurrently with my native iOS maps (which handles the turn by turn work). Waze provides the audio alerts for police, hazards and so on. One major irritation: Waze audio come in about twice the volume of maps. Also irritating are the start up screens that are a serious pain when driving and trying to clear the stupid screen to get to the main display... Marking the location of police activity is simple and straightforward... The use of the other icons are not so intuitiv, though I\'ve never really bothered to figure them out. When making a long trip I found the limitation of a max trip of 1,000 miles also irritating (hence the dual use of maps to nav and Waze to alert.', '116061067', 'applestore', 'France', 'Excellent ... but !!!', 'GPS at the top! On the other hand it is very annoying for the location to have the choice only on the position Never or Always. As soon as it is possible to use Waze with the GPS position when the application is active, I will vote 5 stars. Google Maps makes it ...', 'Waze', 0.213131, 2, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 674, -1, 0, 0.875, 'ot', 'ot'),
('87455440', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Best streaming music service, its that simple.', 'Pretty much tried them all, keep coming back to Spotify.  Apple Music is a close 2nd, but does a poor job of recommending new music.  Ex. I select lots of rock and rap to set my preferences, yet it tries to help me \"discover\" country songs? ?. No thanks.  Sticking with Spotify until a worthy challenger steps up.  Great job.', '499502104', 'applestore', 'France', 'Better than the', 'Deezer is set KO by spotify ????', 'Spotify', 0.0916682, 2, 1, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 675, 1, 0, 0.875, 'ot', 'ot');
